The case appears to set a precedent, since there is no law in the state of Massachusetts that makes it a crime to incite suicide.
Carter was 17 when Roy was found dead of carbon monoxide poisoning in a car in 2014.
The case drew national attention when it emerged that Carter had incited her boyfriend to commit suicide in his text messages.
