His energy is transmitted from the screen."
News crews have long since left Ferguson, but relations between the community and police remain strained.
Ferrell still has two-and-a-half years of probation remaining. He was convicted of blocking a highway at a demonstration.
His description of the sociopolitical climate in his home neighborhood is short and succinct: "A shambles."
