Companies have realised they need to follow workplace culture so they don't become the next Uber. There has been turmoil around the transport company ever since a former employee wrote on his blog about a culture where employees are harassed and those who talk about problems are punished.
For startups like Glint, such omissions are an attractive business opportunity.
Corporate governance, regulation and compliance is a global industry whose value could reach more than $118.7 billion by 2020, according to Let's Talk Payments.
Convercent, based in Denver, Colorado, is a startup that helps companies detect and prevent inappropriate behavior. Interest in the company surged earlier this year when Uber's reputation took a battering.
