From the perspective of jobs, wages and livelihoods, as well as Brexit, the rising cost of living and the continued curtailment of production, east Glasgow desperately needs a successful McVitie's."
A Pladis spokesman said the factory manager had only received the trade union letter the day before and the company is responding to the letter directly because it appreciates the ongoing interaction with workers and trade union representatives.
"We had a regular meeting with employees and GMB representatives in Tollcross two months ago, when we openly discussed a number of issues.
Among other things, we discussed with employees the fact that, like other companies operating in highly competitive and uncertain markets, we continuously evaluate all our businesses and locations in order to maintain our competitiveness."
A spokesman said the company had invested more than £5m in the Tollcross plant in recent years, most notably in its production lines and operational improvements.
"We are aware of Tollcross' long history as a manufacturing facility and will certainly be the first to let employees and union representatives know if we intend to make any changes to the plant's operations."
Did PSG warn Barcelona about Neymar's transfer three years ago?
LaLiga may regret interest in Marco Verratti
Paris Saint-Germain will not give up pursuit of Neymar after paying a £189m transfer fee to close the deal. But did PSG warn Barcelona of a record transfer three years ago?
The sensational move is the most talked about incident of the summer. The team in France's Ligue 1 football league are poised to break the world record for transfer totals. The previous record was less than half as low: it was created when Paul Pogba returned to Manchester United in an £89m transfer.
Following the transfer, Neymar will become the world's most expensive footballer and also the highest-paid professional athlete in the world, with PSG offering him a salary of more than £500,000 a week after tax.
Barcelona are known to be furious with PSG's performance and the way Neymar has forcibly left the club. A source close to Barcelona says the club have taken very good care of Neymar since he arrived at Santos in 2013.
Did the PSG chairman warn the football world about this move three years ago?
When Manchester City announced their interest in Blaise Matuidi in 2014, Nasser Al-Khelaifi warned clubs seeking PSG's best players.
"I am not worried, as they know that if they are after our players, we will become their opponent and we will contact their players," Al-Khelaifi said.
"We respect all the clubs.
But if they're after our players, they're going to have to face the consequences.'
Barcelona appear guilty of doing just that: expressing an interest in PSG midfielder Marco Verratti earlier this summer.
PSG made it clear it would not let the Italian leave under any circumstances. It may well be that Barcelona will lose their star player Neymar as a result.
